Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with problems involving points and lines in the plane and their extensions to higher dimensions.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves counting problems and equivalence classes.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses homotheties, which are transformations commonly used in game theory.
- cs.MG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as homotheties can be used in data augmentation techniques in machine learning.
- cs.SD (Sound) is the least likely category as the paper does not seem to involve any sound-related research.
